            <h1>Verbs</h1>

            <h2>Present tense</h2>

            <p>Verbs in the present tense have 7 different forms, or conjugations. The stem of the word and 6 conjugations based on who is doing the speaking, for example, "to run".</p>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Subject</th>
                        <th>Читати</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Я</td>
                        <td>Читаю</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Ти</td>
                        <td>Читаєш</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Він/Вона/Воно</td>
                        <td>Читає</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Ви</td>
                        <td>Читаєте</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Ми</td>
                        <td>Читаємо</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Вони</td>
                        <td>Читають</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <p>The above is an example of the first form of conjugation. There are two multiple forms of conjugation, they depend on the ending of the verb. There are also quite a few exceptions that do not fall under either rule and must simple be memorized. First, lets take a look at conjugation 1.</p>

            <h3>Conjuation 1</h3>

            <p>The first conjugation form is for verbs that end with "-ати", "-яти" or "-вати". 
        </div>
